		<div>There is a gazillion posts and threads about manaburn, many of which have valid complaints.<br />
<br />
My impression is that they consider them to be nothing more than a minority of players who whine and moan on the boards and if they just ignore it, it will die down, aka the fishing and tribute nerf after the release of GoD. The difference with the manaburn issue however is that from day one there have been posts and threads about it. People have not given up.<br />
<br />
Lately though I think they may be starting to circle the wagons, as evident by the cancellation of the January summit and the silence from them. Either they don't have the manpower and resources to start tweaking the class balance thing, or just don't want to until this whole thing about the decrease in server population and effects of the other games out there sheds some light on the long term future of EQ.</div>
